A few notable observations I have made from the get go:
  
The root disk has a 95% usage 
    Risk Level: High
    Full disk can potentially corrupt databases, crash services, prevent logging. This is a hosting issue but worth documenting nonetheless
    Potential fixes: Increasing the host server size or moving it to a disk where there is more space, cleaning up any unneccesary files on the disk.

Server Load 9.41 on 32 cpus (around 0.3 per core)
  Risk Level: Low-Medium
  Fine but could potentially lead to problems such as slowing and freezing if usage increases.

PhpmyAdmin is reachable if the user doesn't clear their browser and isn't suffiently protected. Cookie is visible on screen in the URL.
  Risk Level: Medium-High
  2 Factor authentication is ideal for any admin portals and the credentials to get to the control panel are an easy target for bruteforce. This could lead to attackers to gaining access to the control panel and Admin portal and altering
  the code for the website as well altering the website to display things to further their agendas (Hacktivists etc.). Could also potentially hyjack the domain which could lead to a ransomware attack.

